  regular hexagon rules
 sides are equilateral  

 In the pointy orientation, 
 a hexagon has width 
 w = sqrt(3) * size 
 and 
 height 
 h = 2 * size. 
 The sqrt(3) comes from sin(60°).

 sizeHex = radius to all 6 angles
 width w = sqrt(3) //sqrt(3)
height h = 2 * size
